article.headline: Princeton 73, College of N.J. 40
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Kareem Maddox scored 21 points and grabbed 12 rebounds as Princeton routed College of New Jersey 73-40 on Sunday. The Tigers (12-4) shot 51.7 percent from the field (31 of 60) and dominated the boards, outrebounding New Jersey 42-26. The Lions (3-14) led for three minutes midway through the first half, before Princeton caught them and pulled away. After Steve Siracusa's jump shot tied it 18-18 with 10:44 to play in the first half, the Tigers went on a 15-2 run to create some breathing room. Douglas Davis' jumper with 1:38 left capped the run and made it 33-22 and Princeton led 34-25 at halftime. Princeton went on a 22-2 run midway through the second half that sealed the game. It turned a 41-31 lead into a 63-33 blowout with 6:06 left. Davis added 12 points for Princeton. College of New Jersey was led by Donovan Smalls' 13 points and Siracusa's 12.
